CHAPTER 1: 

The clouds never seemed to lift and rain poured down persistently on this dapple-gray planet. I hopped into the Scud, beat-up, had to jump-start it, always made me nervous when the Scud didn’t start up, I knew that raiders were numerous in these parts, the last place I wanted to be stuck. so deployed the sensors, so he could see what was prowling about. Hit the steering wheel, spate out a curse or two before it rumbled to life. Put it into gear and it glided slowly down the forested path. “Stinking, rotten planet,” I muttered to himself. “No good”
